message.content: cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.TYPES, cs.SY - This paper deals with the semantics and reasoning principles of gradually typed languages, which are typically studied in the programming languages (cs.PL) and logic (cs.LO) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of embedding-projection pairs (ep pairs) for proving graduality, which is a topic that falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and type theory (cs.TYPES) sub-categories. Finally, the paper touches on the interpretation of type dynamism, which is a concept related to subtyping and falls under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
